The Senate gave voice vote approval Tuesday to 
the nomination of Ronald F Lehman to be the Pentagons new 
assistant secretary of defense for international security 
Lehman replaces Richard N Perle who resigned in December to 
return to private life 
Lehman moves to the Pentagon from the White House where he 
helped negotiate the Intermediaterange Nuclear Forces treaty which 
is now pending in the Senate 
